Cell[TextData[{
 "Calculate the same quantity giving the Green's function in the Nambu form \
with the off-diagonal block of fictitious anomalous Green's functions. In \
this case,  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["BravyiLogarithmicNegativity"]], 
    "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiLogarithmicNegativity", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "4e2b9924-4c8d-4da8-b77d-d413f7cd19be"],
 " uses a method based on the coherent-state representation of fermionic \
Gaussian states (",
 ButtonBox["Shapourian and Ryu, 2017",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevB.95.165101"], None}],
 "; ",
 ButtonBox["Shapourian and Ryu, 2019a",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevA.99.022310"], None}],
 "). The current implementation is unstable when any eigenvalue of the matrix \
of Green's functions approaches 1 (corresponding to an empty single-particle \
level), which here is avoided by the construction of Green's functions in the \
above."
}], "ExampleText",
 CellID->2127532502,ExpressionUUID->"b9355ebf-22f7-48f0-af54-2c9c5d1c6b39"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"nbu", "=", 
  RowBox[{"NambuGreen", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"grn", ",", "0"}], "}"}], "]"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"nbu", "//", "ArrayShort"}]}], "Input",
 CellProlog:>Needs["QuantumMob`Q3`"],
 CellLabel->"In[5]:=",
 CellID->1817924080,ExpressionUUID->"cf913336-363a-4d74-b687-8d185ead4134"],

