   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 52, 52.153520}", 
    "history" -> {"14.0", "14.1", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "partial transposition", "partial time-reversal transform"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiLogarithmicNegativity[grn, {k1, k2, ...}] returns the logarithmic \
entanglement negativity between the subsystem consisting of fermion modes \
{k1, k2, ...} \\[Subset] {1, 2, ..., n} in the Bravyi state characterized by \
n*n matrix grn of single-particle Green's functions. \
BravyiLogarithmicNegativity[NambuGreen[{grn, anm}], {k1, k2, ...}] or \
BravyiLogarithmicNegativity[{grn, anm}, {k1, k2, ...}] returns the \
logarithmic negativity in the Bravyi state characterized by n*n matrices grn \
and anm of normal and anomalous Green's functions, respectively. \
BravyiLogarithmicNegativity[state, {k1, k2, ...}] is equivalent to \
BravyiLogarithmicNegativity[BravyiGreen[state], {k1, k2, ...}] for Bravyi \
state. BravyiLogarithmicNegativity[{k1, k2, ...}] is an operator form of \
BravyiLogarithmicNegativity to be applied to Green's functions or Bravyi \
state.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "BravyiLogarithmicNegativity", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> 
    "", "windowtitle" -> "BravyiLogarithmicNegativity", "type" -> "Symbol", 
    "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiLogarithmicNegativity"}},
